  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nVersion: 1.9.13-stable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [65 64 63]\r\nGo Version: go1.14.2\r\nOperating System: darwin\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/local/Cellar/go/1.14.2_1/libexec\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n'eth.pendingTransactions' returns a series of pending transactions\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n'eth.pendingTransactions' doesn't return any pending transactions\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\ncurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_pendingTransactions\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}' http://localhost:8545\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nThe client is synchronous which can be verified by running 'eth.syncing' which returns false.\r\n\r\nThere does exist pending transactions which can be verified by running 'txpool.content' which returns a series of pending transactions.\r\n\r\nBut 'eth.pendingTransaction' returns an empty set of pending transactions\r\n",
